Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.75,0:00:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The dreams embraced by a single life{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.76,0:00:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}are boundless beyond even the stars.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.76,0:00:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The dreams that we foster over time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.77,0:00:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}are waiting for the moment\N{\c&He1e1e1&}when we come upon them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.45,0:00:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The words we exchange\N{\c&He1e1e1&}make our hearts tremble,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.45,0:00:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}and a chance meeting\N{\c&He1e1e1&}could change the future.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.79,0:01:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}People, no matter who they are,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}as they pursue their dreams,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.07,0:01:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}have the courage to travel new paths.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.74,0:01:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}As we leave behind a living\N{\c&He1e1e1&}testament of our journey,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.08,0:01:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}the Galaxy Railways on which\N{\c&He1e1e1&}we travel continue ever on.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.44,0:01:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}All people are like travelers,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}in search of happiness.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.78,0:01:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Those that believe in a star of hope\N{\c&He1e1e1&}embark on a lonesome journey.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.13,0:02:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}However, in some cases, destiny imposes\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a senseless darkness upon their hearts.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.74,0:02:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Shrieking in the Darkness"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.17,0:02:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I've apprehended him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.85,0:03:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Reckless fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.46,0:03:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That completes all of the patterns, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.46,0:03:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Come here a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.47,0:03:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Do you know where you messed up?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.47,0:03:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you don't... I'll show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.15,0:03:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.48,0:03:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're too soft, rookie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.49,0:03:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Can you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.15,0:03:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If that hadn't been broken,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you'd have kicked the bucket just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.49,0:03:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}J- just a minute, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.50,0:03:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Really? That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.84,0:03:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.47,0:04:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Mama, look.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.47,0:04:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.14,0:04:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.48,0:04:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ladies and gentlemen, please remain calm.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}We ask that you remain in your seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.49,0:04:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Rachel, put this on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.16,0:04:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's going on, Mama?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.83,0:05:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's all right. See? Lil-{\i1}chan{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&}is right here with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.12,0:05:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Cut it out already, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.78,0:05:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You can't just take someone's gun, to say\N{\c&He1e1e1&}nothing of pulling the trigger on them!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.66,0:05:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's going too far, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.12,0:05:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you listening to me, Bruce!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.80,0:05:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This soft drink...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.47,0:05:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There are limits to how\N{\c&He1e1e1&}soft something should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.47,0:05:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you going on about, with the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}"soft" this and the "soft" that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.14,0:05:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How long are you going to keep treating\N{\c&He1e1e1&}me like a rookie before you're satisfied?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.48,0:05:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Where's the problem in treating\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a rookie like a rookie?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.48,0:05:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's not what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.55,0:05:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What I'm saying is,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I can't return to duty like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.82,0:05:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Receiving emergency signal!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.82,0:05:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}An accident of unknown origin\N{\c&He1e1e1&}has occurred aboard
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.09,0:06:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The No. 323 Express,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}bound for Greater Magellan!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.83,0:06:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Scale and details are unknown.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Its identification signal has terminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.77,0:06:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Contact has been lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.43,0:06:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Spica, Vega, and Sirius Platoons,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}please report to the scene at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.10,0:06:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sirius Platoon, move out!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.78,0:06:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let me give you one word of warning...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.71,0:06:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}don't go thinking that gutsy-ass\N{\c&He1e1e1&}enthusiasm of yours can solve everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.45,0:06:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I- I don't need you to tell me that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.79,0:06:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}System check!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.12,0:06:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}System check, standby.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.79,0:06:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Particle warpspeed\N{\c&He1e1e1&}generators reading normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.46,0:06:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ascent Float lock confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.13,0:06:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Gravitational barrier\N{\c&He1e1e1&}generator systems normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.80,0:06:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Engage main circuits.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.47,0:06:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Engaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.81,0:06:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Flame Swallow--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.81,0:06:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We're going first, Julia!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.81,0:06:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Iron Berger{\i0}, move out!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.48,0:06:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey! Murase!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.15,0:06:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Vega Platoon, please perform\N{\c&He1e1e1&}safety check before departing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.82,0:07:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You dumbasses! This is no\N{\c&He1e1e1&}time to be taking it easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.15,0:07:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Of all the...! Following Vega Platoon,\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Flame Swallow{\i0}, move out!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.77,0:07:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Big One{\i0}, move out!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.80,0:07:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sheesh. That's five times\N{\c&He1e1e1&}in a row it's been tails.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.47,0:07:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Manabu...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.47,0:07:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Make sure you take things\N{\c&He1e1e1&}more seriously than normal today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.14,0:07:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.14,0:07:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's the matter?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Is there some problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.48,0:08:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What do you think it means when\N{\c&He1e1e1&}they send three platoons all at once
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.28,0:08:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}to a scene where the details are unknown?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.08,0:08:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.08,0:08:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You mean they're assuming\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the worst case possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.09,0:08:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You've got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.09,0:08:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Those who came to rescue could wind up\N{\c&He1e1e1&}being those who need rescuing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.45,0:08:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This would make\N{\c&He1e1e1&}communications impossible, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.45,0:08:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It sure would.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.45,0:08:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Men!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.45,0:08:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's possible that\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}No. 323{\i0} has been shot at.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.46,0:08:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Be ready for them in case\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the shooters come back!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.79,0:08:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Silver, you stay in the gunnery car!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.80,0:08:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Copy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.13,0:08:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Maggie, patrol the area in your fighter\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to a radius of 20 spacekilos.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.47,0:08:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Search and rescue any passengers\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that were thrown clear...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.14,0:08:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}...from the jolt of the accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.81,0:09:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.08,0:09:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Jose!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.74,0:09:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You fly escort for her!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.41,0:09:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.75,0:09:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We will join the other two platoons in\N{\c&He1e1e1&}searching the area here for survivors.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.75,0:09:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you find anyone, take them\N{\c&He1e1e1&}at once to the ambulance car.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.09,0:09:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.45,0:09:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Damn...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.78,0:09:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is nasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.78,0:09:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Everything is in pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.79,0:09:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't tell me there\N{\c&He1e1e1&}aren't any survivors...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.79,0:09:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No luck here. Everything is all scorched.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.47,0:10:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This was no accident,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that's for sure. It was shot...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.14,0:10:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No... it was bombed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.81,0:10:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.81,0:10:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.15,0:10:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, Sirius Platoon!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.82,0:10:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Do something with this guy, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.72,0:10:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He's in our way, and we can't\N{\c&He1e1e1&}do anything with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.83,0:10:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki! Calm down and breathe!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.83,0:10:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He's having a panic attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.16,0:10:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.50,0:10:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.83,0:10:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}have Yuuki stand down on {\i1}Big One{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.17,0:10:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.52,0:10:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, this one's alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.52,0:10:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We've found a survivor!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.52,0:10:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's a child! A girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.19,0:10:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}--What's her condition?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}--She's wearing a life jacket, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.19,0:11:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Her oxygen is leaking! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.86,0:11:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuki, we're bringing her to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.13,0:11:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Copy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.81,0:11:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.49,0:11:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuki, will she recover?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.49,0:11:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm doing my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.49,0:11:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}M- my... Lil...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.50,0:11:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}T- thank... you... Big... Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.18,0:11:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Mama...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.85,0:12:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Say... where's... Mama...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.13,0:12:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Mama... where are you...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.48,0:12:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Father! Don't go!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.83,0:12:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It can't be...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.83,0:12:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.84,0:12:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Can't you do anything?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Can't you do anything else!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.84,0:12:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Do something, Yuki! Help her!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.84,0:12:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki-{\i1}san{\i0}, please calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.51,0:13:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}--Yuki, please! Please!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}--Please, let go of me, Yuuki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.51,0:13:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}--Yuki!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}--Let go!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.12,0:13:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.12,0:13:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki Manabu,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.79,0:13:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm placing you on suspension.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.47,0:13:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}As a result of our\N{\c&He1e1e1&}investigation and examination,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.14,0:13:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}we have determined that this\N{\c&He1e1e1&}incident was not an accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.51,0:13:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}but an act of man--a terrorist bombing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.15,0:13:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We believe that a subatomic\N{\c&He1e1e1&}particle-dissolving type of bomb was used.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.82,0:13:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Due to its nature, it is difficult\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to pinpoint where the bomb was set,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.83,0:13:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}so we have not determined\N{\c&He1e1e1&}in which locations,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.50,0:13:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}as well as how many bombs\N{\c&He1e1e1&}were hidden aboard {\i1}No. 323{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.83,0:13:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Have there been any statements\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from opposition groups?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.50,0:13:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Currently, we have not been able to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}confirm any claims of responsibility,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.24,0:14:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}nor any warnings of\N{\c&He1e1e1&}further opposition from anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.44,0:14:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So we don't know what\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the objective was, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.11,0:14:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's possible the culprit just\N{\c&He1e1e1&}did it for the thrill of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.11,0:14:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It couldn't be...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.78,0:14:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.12,0:14:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}From now on, in addition to taking\N{\c&He1e1e1&}greater precautions on all lines,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.46,0:14:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and watch out for any movements\N{\c&He1e1e1&}by criminal organizations
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.86,0:14:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}in every star system,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the space mafia, and pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.80,0:14:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}--Roger.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}--Roger.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}--Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.80,0:14:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.47,0:14:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you here for?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.14,0:14:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I thought I said you were on suspension.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.48,0:14:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How long is my suspension?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.14,0:14:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Indefinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.48,0:14:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Think about what course of action\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you're going take.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.78,0:14:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't come back until\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you've made a decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.15,0:14:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.82,0:14:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Think hard about whether you're up\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to the same kind of duty
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.39,0:14:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}that your father and brother\N{\c&He1e1e1&}gave their lives for.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.50,0:15:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You are still young. There are any number\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of other jobs you could start over with.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.77,0:15:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.11,0:15:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Your choice of words is too harsh!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.44,0:15:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I can't blame him for saying so.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.45,0:15:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}I haven't been able to do anything.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.45,0:15:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Want to bet on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.13,0:15:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey there, Manabu-{\i1}chan{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.46,0:15:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Judging from the look on your face,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you haven't eaten breakfast, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.13,0:15:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Here. Eat this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.47,0:15:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank you, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.14,0:15:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You can't survive in space\N{\c&He1e1e1&}if you don't eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.67,0:15:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Eat it, if even just half of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.81,0:15:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let go of me! Let go, I said!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.48,0:15:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Cheapskate! You can at least let me\N{\c&He1e1e1&}have a little look, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.15,0:15:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You cannot. It is against the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.15,0:15:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let go!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.15,0:15:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I just want to see the\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Fort Worth's{\i0} cockpit this one time!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.16,0:16:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Conductor-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.16,0:16:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Manabu-{\i1}chan{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.16,0:16:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Would you let that boy go for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.10,0:16:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But according to the rules, I must\N{\c&He1e1e1&}take all trespassers into custody...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.77,0:16:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.44,0:16:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.44,0:16:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Just look! I must insist\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that you do not touch!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.11,0:16:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You shouldn't go overly\N{\c&He1e1e1&}easy on him, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.78,0:16:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He may be a child, but he is\N{\c&He1e1e1&}still a trespasser, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.62,0:16:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You have to deal with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.46,0:16:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Long ago, there was a tragic\N{\c&He1e1e1&}accident here in Destiny Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.13,0:16:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't know what happened\N{\c&He1e1e1&}here in the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.47,0:16:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}but if there's anything that I can do...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.81,0:16:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Father... Big Brother Mamoru...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.15,0:16:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}I wasn't able to do anything...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.85,0:17:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Am I nothing more than a\N{\c&He1e1e1&}star-struck, spoiled dreamer?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.76,0:17:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yo, train mechanic!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.76,0:17:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you doing,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}skipping work out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.10,0:17:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I was just...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.43,0:17:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're a rookie, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.77,0:17:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.43,0:17:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.10,0:17:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're not at all used to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}putting your back into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.54,0:17:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You won't get any girls that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.77,0:17:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm Kayamori Shaw,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the song-and-dance vendor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.04,0:17:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The operators around\N{\c&He1e1e1&}headquarters here know me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.78,0:17:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Manabu, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.78,0:17:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah. Yuuki Manabu.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.12,0:17:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you've got the time,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}tag along with me for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.79,0:17:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So that's it. You goofed up\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and got suspended, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.10,0:17:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's just what Old Lady Kinuko figured.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.13,0:17:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The old lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.47,0:17:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}She asked me to talk to you, saying you\N{\c&He1e1e1&}wouldn't be able to think decently
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.97,0:17:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}if you were left alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.14,0:17:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}For Pete's sake... What a busybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.47,0:17:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh, don't call her that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.54,0:18:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There's a good reason why the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}old lady is getting involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.15,0:18:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}She has lost a child. If he had lived,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}he would be just about our age now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.09,0:18:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't you feel like helping me out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.76,0:18:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh, I just remembered...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.77,0:18:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The vending machines next to the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Alert Room don't seem to be working right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.44,0:18:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's strange. They just barely\N{\c&He1e1e1&}replaced the ones for the train section.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.44,0:18:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The trains? No, that's not what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.45,0:18:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's okay, I'll take a look at them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.81,0:18:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Can I ask you to get me\N{\c&He1e1e1&}another case from out of the back?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.78,0:18:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.47,0:18:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Well, what is it? You look like\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you want to ask me something.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.81,0:19:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Do you want to get Yuuki-{\i1}kun{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to quit the SDF?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.74,0:19:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki will decide for himself\N{\c&He1e1e1&}whether or not he quits.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.41,0:19:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I can't understand why you would\N{\c&He1e1e1&}act so detached toward him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.75,0:19:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It wouldn't mean anything\N{\c&He1e1e1&}if we hound him to make a decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.49,0:19:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If he doesn't decide on his own,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}he'll be left with regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.09,0:19:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}His dreams and his infatuation for--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.76,0:19:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is it so wrong to choose a job\N{\c&He1e1e1&}out of dreams and infatuation?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.10,0:19:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The problem is his commitment afterward.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.76,0:19:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I think he's committed, in his own way.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}He's showing it through his actions, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.10,0:19:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain, were you always so\N{\c&He1e1e1&}matter-of-fact when you started?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.11,0:19:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.11,0:19:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain, I don't think\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you're giving Yuuki-{\i1}kun{\i0}--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.44,0:19:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That will be all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.78,0:19:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Receiving emergency signal!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}The No. 224 Express on the Altair Line,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.12,0:19:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}as well as the No. 811 Express on the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Regulus Main Line, have lost contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.13,0:19:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.13,0:20:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Nothing. This just reminds me of\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the Ramen house my family owns.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.80,0:20:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You don't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.80,0:20:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}My mom is running it by herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.81,0:20:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Come on in!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.48,0:20:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Shaw...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.48,0:20:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't you carry Tabito Tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.48,0:20:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Tabito Tea? Oh, they don't\N{\c&He1e1e1&}make that any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.48,0:20:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The flavor was too distinctive,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and it didn't sell.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.82,0:20:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're kidding me! Tea that delicious...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.16,0:20:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're an odd one, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.76,0:20:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Well, I guess it was only\N{\c&He1e1e1&}received well around Tabito.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.36,0:20:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Wait, do you come from Tabito?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.84,0:20:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The SDF is scrambling, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.51,0:20:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Mankind sometimes learns how powerless\N{\c&He1e1e1&}they are, and find themselves at a loss.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.52,0:20:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}You must not stop, Manabu.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.86,0:20:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}My pure little soul...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.53,0:21:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Sudden darkness...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.53,0:21:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}It comes to everyone.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.46,0:21:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Those who continue to wander in it...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.80,0:21:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}...are the ones who discover the light.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.47,0:21:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}And for who learn the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}truth of their hearts,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.94,0:21:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}that may be their destiny.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.83,0:21:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}How many nights have I\N{\c&He1e1e1&}spent alone since then?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.84,0:22:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Constantly having dreams of the hope\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that you are, as I lightly sleep.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.53,0:22:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The smiles and tears that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you gave to me and me alone{\i0}
